obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12611)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12611&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Commissions for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `((2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2. 5th February, 2007, vide notification No. S.O. 229(E), dated 15th February, 2007, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12612)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12612&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission or of the State Commission, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) "child rights" includes the children's rights adopted in the United Nations convention on`
  line `the Rights of the Child on the 20th November, 1989 and ratified by the Government of India on`
  line `the 11th December, 1992;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights constituted`
  line `under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Member" means a Member of the Commission or of the State Commission, as the case`
  line `may be, and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "State Commission" means a State Commission for Protection of Child Rights constituted`
  line `under section 17.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12613)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of National Commission for Protection of Child Rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12613&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification, constitute a body to be known as the National Commission for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned`
  line `to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of the following Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson who is a person of eminence and has done outstanding work for promoting`
  line `the welfare of children; and`
  line
  line `(b) six Members, out of which at least two shall be women, from the following fields, to be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of eminence, ability, integrity,`
  line `standing and experience in,--`
  line
  line `(i) education;`
  line
  line `(ii) child health, care, welfare or child development;`
  line
  line `(iii) juvenile justice or care of neglected or marginalized children or children with`
  line disabilities;
  line
  line `(iv) elimination of child labour or children in distress;`
  line
  line `(v) child psychology or sociology; and`
  line
  line `(vi) laws relating to children.`
  line
  line `(3) The office of the Commission shall be at Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12614)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12614&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, appoint the Chairperson and other Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall be appointed on the recommendation of a three member`
  line `Selection Committee constituted by the Central Government under the Chairmanship of the ^1`
  line [Minister
  line `in-charge of the Ministry or the Department of Women and Child Development].`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2007, s.2., for "Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Human Resource Development"`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-12-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12615)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12615&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Chairperson and every Member shall hold office as such for a term of three years from the date on`
  line `which he assumes office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or a Member shall hold the office for more than two terms:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Chairperson or any other Member shall hold office as such after he has`
  line attained--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairperson, the age of sixty-five years; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Member, the age of sixty years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or a Member may, by writing under his hand addressed to the Central`
  line `Government, resign his office at any time.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12616)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Salary and allowances of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12616&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The salary and allowances payable`
  line `to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and Members, shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the Chairperson or a Member, as the case may be, shall be varied to his disadvantage after his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12617)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Removal from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12617&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the Chairperson may`
  line `be removed from his office by an order of the Central Government on the ground of proved`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may by order`
  line `remove from office the Chairperson or any other Member, if the Chairperson or, as the case may be,`
  line `such other Member,--`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) refuses to act or becomes incapable of acting; or`
  line
  line `(d) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his office as to render his continuance in office detrimental to the public`
  line `interest; or`
  line
  line `(f) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(g) is, without obtaining leave of absence from the Commission, absent from three`
  line `consecutive meetings of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall be removed under this section until that person has been given an opportunity`
  line `of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12618)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Vacation of office by Chairperson or Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12618&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Chairperson or, as the case may`
  line `be, a Member,--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) tenders his resignation under sub-section (2) of section 5,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(2) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairperson or a Member, whether by reason of`
  line `his death, resignation or otherwise, such vacancy shall be filled within a period of ninety days by`
  line `making afresh appointment in accordance with the provisions of section 4and the person so appointed`
  line `shall hold office for the remainder of the term of office for which the Chairperson, or a Member, as`
  line `the case may be, in whose place he is so appointed would have held that office.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12619)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12619&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the`
  line `Commission shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Commission; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person as the Chairperson or a Member; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Commission not affecting the merits of the case`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12620)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure for transaction of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12620&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet regularly at its`
  line `office at such time as the Chairperson thinks fit, but three months shall not intervene between its last`
  line `and the next meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) All decisions at a meeting shall be taken by majority:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of equality of votes, the Chairperson, or in his absence the person`
  line `presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
  line
  line `(3) If for any reason, the Chairperson, is unable to attend the meeting of the Commission, any`
  line `Member chosen by the Members present from amongst themselves at the meeting, shall preside.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall observe such rules of procedure in the transaction of its business at a`
  line `meeting, including the quorum at such meeting, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the Member-Secretary`
  line `or any other officer of the Commission duly authorised by Member-Secretary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12621)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Member-Secretary, officers and other employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12621&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification, appoint an officer not below the rank of the Joint Secretary or the`
  line `Additional Secretary to the Government of India as a Member-Secretary of the Commission and shall`
  line `make available to the Commission such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the`
  line `efficient performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Member-Secretary shall be responsible for the proper administration of the affairs of the`
  line `Commission and its day-to-day management and shall exercise and discharge such other powers and`
  line `perform such other duties as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Member-Secretary, other officers and employees, appointed for the purpose of the Commission shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12622)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Salaries and allowances to be paid out of grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12622&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to`
  line `the Chairperson and Members and the administrative expenses, including salaries, allowances and`
  line `pensions payable to the Member-Secretary, other officers and employees referred to in section 11,`
  line `shall be paid out of the grants referred to in sub-section (1) of section 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12623)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Functions of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12623&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall perform all or any of the following`
  line `functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) examine and review the safeguards provided by or under any law for the time being in`
  line `force for the protection of child rights and recommend measures for their effective`
  line implementation;
  line
  line `(b) present to the Central Government, annually and at such other intervals, as the`
  line `Commission may deem fit, reports upon the working of those safeguards;`
  line
  line `(c) inquire into violation of child rights and recommend initiation of proceedings in such`
  line cases;
  line
  line `(d) examine all factors that inhibit the enjoyment of rights of children affected by terrorism,`
  line `communal violence, riots, natural disaster, domestic violence, HIV/AIDS, trafficking,`
  line `maltreatment, torture and exploitation, pornography and prostitution and recommend appropriate`
  line `remedial measures;`
  line
  line `(e) look into the matters relating to children in need of special care and protection including`
  line `children in distress, marginalized and disadvantaged children, children in conflict with law,juveniles, children without family and children of prisoners and recommend appropriate remedial`
  line measures;
  line
  line `(f) study treaties and other international instruments and undertake periodical review of`
  line `existing policies, programmes and other activities on child rights and make recommendations for`
  line `their effective implementation in the best interest of children;`
  line
  line `(g) undertake and promote research in the field of child rights;`
  line
  line `(h) spread child rights literacy among various sections of the society and promote awareness`
  line `of the safeguards available for protection of these rights through publications, the media, seminars`
  line `and other available means;`
  line
  line `(i) inspect or cause to be inspected any juvenile custodial home, or any other place of`
  line `residence or institution meant for children, under the control of the Central Government or any`
  line `State Government or any other authority, including any institution run by a social organisation;`
  line `where children are detained or lodged for the purpose of treatment, reformation or protection and`
  line `take up with these authorities for remedial action, if found necessary;`
  line
  line `(j) inquire into complaints and take suo motu notice of matters relating to,--`
  line
  line `(i) deprivation and violation of child rights;`
  line
  line `(ii) non-implementation of laws providing for protection and development of children;`
  line
  line `(iii) non-compliance of policy decisions, guidelines or instructions aimed at mitigating`
  line `hardships to and ensuring welfare of the children and to provide relief to such children,`
  line
  line `or take up the issues arising out of such matters with appropriate authorities; and`
  line
  line `(k) such other functions as it may consider necessary for the promotion of child rights and any`
  line `other matter incidental to the above functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall not inquire into any matter which is pending before a State`
  line `Commission or any other Commission duly constituted under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12624)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Powers relating to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12624&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall, while inquiring into any matter`
  line `referred to in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 13 have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and, in particular, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have the power to forward any case to a Magistrate having jurisdiction`
  line `to try the same and the Magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the`
  line `complaint against the accused as if the case has been forwarded to him under section 346 of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12625)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Steps after inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12625&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Commission may take any of the following steps upon the`
  line `completion of an inquiry held under this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the inquiry discloses, the Commission of violation of child rights of a serious nature`
  line `or contravention of provisions of any law for the time being in force, it may recommend to the`
  line `concerned Government or authority the initiation of proceedings for prosecution or such other`
  line `action as the Commission may deem fit against the concerned person or persons;`
  line
  line `(ii) approach the Supreme Court or the High Court concerned for such directions, orders or`
  line `writs as that Court may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(iii) recommend to the concerned Government or authority for the grant of such interim relief`
  line `to the victim or the members of his family as the Commission may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12626)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Annual and special reports of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12626&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall submit an annual`
  line `report to the Central Government and to the State Government concerned and may at any time submit`
  line `special reports on any matter which, in its opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it should not`
  line `be deferred till submission of the annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government and the State Government concerned, as the case maybe, shall cause`
  line `the annual and special reports of the Commission to be laid before each House of Parliament or the`
  line `State Legislature respectively, as the case may be, along with a memorandum of action taken or`
  line `proposed to be taken on the recommendations of the Commission and the reasons for non-acceptance`
  line `of the recommendations, if any, within a period of one year from the date of receipt of such report.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual report shall be prepared in such form, manner and contain such details as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12627)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Constitution of State Commission for Protection of Child Rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12627&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State`
  line `Government may constitute a body to be known as the ..........(name of the State) Commission for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights to exercise the powers conferred upon, and to perform the functions`
  line `assigned to, a State Commission under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission shall consist of the following Members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson who is a person of eminence and has done outstanding work for promoting`
  line `the welfare of children; and`
  line
  line `(b) six Members, out of which at least two shall be women, from the following fields, to be`
  line `appointed by the State Government from amongst persons of eminence, ability, integrity, standing`
  line `and experience in,--`
  line
  line `(i) education;`
  line
  line `(ii) child health, care, welfare or child development;`
  line
  line `(iii) juvenile justice or care of neglected or marginalized children or children with`
  line disabilities;
  line
  line `(iv) elimination of child labour or children in distress;`
  line
  line `(v) child psychology or sociology; and`
  line
  line `(vi) laws relating to children.`
  line
  line `(3) The headquarter of the State Commission shall be at such place as the State Government may,`
  line `by notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12628)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Appointment of Chairperson and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12628&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall, by`
  line `notification, appoint the Chairperson and other Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson shall be appointed on the recommendation of a three Member`
  line `Selection Committee constituted by the State Government under the Chairmanship of the Minister`
  line `in-charge of the Department dealing with children.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12629)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12629&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1)The`
  line `Chairperson and every Member shall hold office as such for a term of three years from the date on`
  line `which he assumes office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or a Member shall hold the office for more than two terms:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no Chairperson or any other Member shall hold office as such after he has`
  line attained--
  line
  line `(a) in the case of Chairperson, the age of sixty-five years; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Member, the age of sixty years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or a Member may, by writing under his hand addressed to the State`
  line `Government, resign his office at any time.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12630)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Salary and allowances and Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12630&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances`
  line `payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and Members shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the Chairperson or a Member, as the case may be, shall be varied to his disadvantage after his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12631)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Secretary, officers and other employees of the State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12631&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall, by notification, appoint an officer not below the rank of the Secretary to the State`
  line `Government as the Secretary of the State Commission and shall make available to the State`
  line `Commission such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the efficient performance of`
  line `its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary shall be responsible for the proper administration of the affairs of the State`
  line `Commission and its day-to-day management and shall exercise and discharge such other powers and`
  line `perform such other duties as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Secretary, other officers and employees, appointed for the purpose of the State Commission shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12632)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Salaries and allowances to be paid out of grants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12632&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to`
  line `the Chairperson and Members and the administrative expenses, including salaries, allowances and`
  line `pensions payable to the Secretary, other officers and employees referred to in section 21, shall be paid`
  line `out of the grants referred to in sub-section (1) of section 28.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12633)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Annual and special reports of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12633&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall submit`
  line `an annual report to the State Government and may at any time submit special reports on any matter`
  line `which, in its opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it should not be deferred till submission of`
  line `the annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall cause all the reports referred to in sub-section (1) to be laid before`
  line `each House of State Legislature, where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature consists`
  line `of one House, before that House along with a memorandum explaining the action taken or proposed to`
  line `be taken on the recommendations relating to the State and the reasons for the non-acceptance, if any,`
  line `of any of such recommendations.`
  line
  line `(3) The annual report shall be prepared in such form, manner and contain such details as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (12634)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Application of certain provisions relating to National Commission for Protection of Child Rights to State Commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12634&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 7, 8, 9, 10,sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13 and sections 14 and 15 shall apply to a State Commission and shall have effect, subject to`
  line `the following modifications, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) references to "Commission" shall be construed as references to "State Commission";`
  line
  line `(b) references to "Central Government" shall be construed as references to "State`
  line `Government"; and`
  line
  line `(c) references to "Member-Secretary" shall be construed as references to "Secretary".`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (12635)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Children’s Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12635&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of providing speedy trial of offences against children or`
  line `of violation of child rights, the State Government may, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of`
  line `the High Court, by notification, specify at least a court in the State or specify, for each district, a Court`
  line `of Session to be a Children's Court to try the said offences:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply if--`
  line
  line `(a) a Court of Session is already specified as a special court; or`
  line
  line `(b) a special court is already constituted, for such offences under any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (12636)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12636&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `For every Children's Court, the State Government shall, by`
  line `notification, specify a Public Prosecutor or appoint an advocate who has been in practice as an`
  line `advocate for not less than seven years, as a Special Public Prosecutor for the purpose of conducting`
  line `cases in that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (12637)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12637&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums of money as it thinks fit for performing the functions`
  line `under this Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (12638)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Grants by State Governments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12638&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Legislature by law in this behalf, pay to the State Commission by way of grants such sums of`
  line `money as the State Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission may spend such sums of money as it thinks fit for performing the`
  line `functions under Chapter III of this Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of`
  line `the grants referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (12639)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Accounts and audit of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12639&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts`
  line `and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall, have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `the authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government by the Commission and the Central Government shall cause the`
  line `audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (12640)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Accounts and audit of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12640&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall maintain proper`
  line `accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of`
  line India.
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the State Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in`
  line `connection with such audit shall be payable by the State Commission to the Comptroller and`
  line Auditor-General.
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the State Commission under this Act shall, have the same rights and`
  line `privileges and the authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `generally has in connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the`
  line `right to demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and`
  line `papers and to inspect any of the offices of the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the State Commission as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the State Government by the State Commission and the State Government shall`
  line `cause the audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (12641)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12641&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government, the State Government, the Commission, the State`
  line `Commission, or any Member thereof or any person acting under the direction either of the Central`
  line `Government, State Government, Commission or the State Commission, in respect of anything which`
  line `is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules made there under`
  line `or in respect of the publication by or under the authority of the Central Government, State`
  line `Government, Commission, or the State Commission of any report or paper.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (12642)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Chairperson, Members and other officers to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12642&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every Member of the`
  line `Commission, State Commission and every officer appointed in the Commission or the State`
  line `Commission to exercise functions under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (12643)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12643&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the discharge of its functions under this Act, the`
  line `Commission shall be guided by such directions on questions of policy relating to national purposes, as`
  line `may be given to it by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If any dispute arises between the Central Government and the Commission as to whether a`
  line `question is or is not a question of policy relating to national purposes, the decision of the Central`
  line `Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (12644)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Returns or information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12644&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall furnish to the Central Government such`
  line `returns or other information with respect to its activities as the Central Government may, from time to`
  line `time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (12645)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12645&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members of the Commission and`
  line `their salaries and allowances under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Commission in the transaction of its business at a`
  line `meeting under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and duties which may be exercised and performed by the Member- Secretary`
  line `of the Commission under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of officers and other`
  line `employees of the Commission under sub-section (3) of section 11; and`
  line
  line `(e) form of the statement of accounts and other records to be prepared by the Commission`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 29.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions afore said, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any`
  line `such modification or annulment shall be with out prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (12646)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12646&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and Members of the State Commission`
  line `and their salaries and allowances under section 20;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the State Commission in the transaction of its business at`
  line `a meeting under sub-section (4) of section 10 read with section24;`
  line
  line `(c) the powers and duties which may be exercised and performed by the Secretary of the State`
  line `Commission under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(d) the salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of officers and other`
  line `employees of the State Commission under sub-section (3) of section 21; and`
  line
  line `(e) form of the statement of accounts and other records to be prepared by the State`
  line `Commission under sub-section (1) of section 30.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where`
  line `such State Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (12647)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700&sectionId=12647&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_17_00001_200604_1517807317700
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such`
  line `provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of the period of two years`
  line `from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
